  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to more easily discern between my incoming and outgoing transactions so that I can understand my transaction history at a glance.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Improvement\r\n\r\n*Summary*:\r\nDuring testing, users had difficulty distinguishing between their sent and received transactions on the Transactions History screen because they are too similar looking.\r\n\r\nCurrently we use purple and green arrows and a “To/From” line to indicate transfer directions. \r\n\r\n![txn history](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15470435/39255461-2abad7fe-48df-11e8-93f9-4fefad79acbc.png)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nWhen a user looks at their transactions history, they do not have to question whether a transaction was incoming or outgoing; visual cues make it perfectly clear.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\n-  Add visual cues to indicate whether a transfer is positive (incoming) or negative (outgoing), with + or - symbols in front of transfer amount.\r\n-  Make either positive or negative transfers stand apart, e.g. with colored font on incoming transactions.\r\n- The color purple isn’t typically associated with a negative transaction; it may be beneficial to use a neutral color for outgoing transaction symbols.\r\n",
